{{Cleanup FJC Bio}}
'''Thomas Roberts McMillen''' (June 8, 1916 &ndash; September 16, 2002) was a [[United States federal judge]].

McMillen was born in [[Decatur, Illinois]]. He received a [[A.B.]] from [[Princeton University]] in 1938. He received a [[LL.B.]] from [[Harvard Law School]] in 1941. He was in the [[United States Army]] from 1941 to 1945. He was in private practice of law in [[Chicago, Illinois]] from 1946 to 1966. He was a judge to the Cook County Circuit Court, Illinois from 1966 to 1971. He was in private practice of law in [[Chicago, Illinois]] from 1985 to 2002. 

McMillen was a federal judge to the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of Illinois]]. McMillen was nominated by President [[Richard M. Nixon]] on March 29, 1971, to a seat vacated by [[William J. Campbell]]. He was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] on April 21, 1971, and received commission on April 23, 1971. Assumed [[senior status]] on December 31, 1984. McMillen<!-- -->'s service was terminated on September 8, 1985, due to retirement.

He died in [[Evanston, Illinois]].

